== WAYPOINTS ==


<table cellspacing="10" style="width:100%">
  
<tr><td width="174">
/dropwaypoints #
</td><td width="219">
0: no waypoints are dropped in game
1: limited number of waypoints are dropped in game (default)
</td></tr>

<tr><td width="174">
/showwaypoints #
</td><td width="219">
toggles the visibility of the path that connects waypoints. Waypoints are always visible if they are being dropped.
</td></tr>

<tr><td width="174">
/savewaypoints
</td><td width="219">
saves a .wpt file containing the current maps waypoints. The default waypoint file is saved as the current map's name.
/savewaypoints customname.wpt will save a waypoint file as a custom name.
</td></tr>

<tr><td width="174">
/loadwaypoints
</td><td width="219">
loads a .wpt file containing waypoints. A waypoint file matching the maps name is loaded by default.
/loadwaypoints customname will load another waypoint file with a custom name.
</td></tr>

<tr><td width="174">
/delselwaypoints
</td><td width="219">
Select the area in which the waypoints you want to remove are. Then use this command to delete the waypoints in the selected area.
</td></tr>